# Privacy: Never Expose User Emails

User emails must never be displayed in audience-facing pages or any public UI. Emails are sensitive PII.

**Where this applies:**

- Page titles
- Links (e.g. "Back to [DJ name]")
- Headings and labels
- Any HTML rendered for unauthenticated visitors

**Use `user.public_name`** for display text in audience-facing views. This returns `display_name` if set, otherwise falls back to `slug`. Never use `user.email` directly.
